    <title>AMD’s best gaming CPU is really difficult to buy during its launch week</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/EPz-52J3kwCjsHwqkqs0GYEH5xo=/9x0:2709x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73708455/247357_AMD_Ryzen_7_9800X3D_TWarren_0001.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Photo by Tom Warren / The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="lCuTs8"&gt;AMD launched its latest &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24288948/amd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-review-cpu-processor-benchmark-test"&gt;Ryzen 7 9800X3D&lt;/a&gt; to glowing reviews this week, but if you’re looking to buy one then you might have to wait for more stock. The 9800X3D is currently sold out &lt;a href="https://click.linksynergy.com/deeplink?id=nOD%2FrLJHOac&amp;amp;mid=44583&amp;amp;u1=verge&amp;amp;murl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newegg.com%2Famd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-ryzen-7-9000-series-granite-ridge-zen-5-socket-am5-processor%2Fp%2FN82E16819113877" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;at Newegg&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://bestbuy.7tiv.net/c/482924/614286/10014?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fsite%2Famd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-8-core-16-thread-3-8-ghz-5-2-ghz-max-boost-socket-am5-unlocked-desktop-processor-silver%2F6606318.p%3FskuId%3D6606318&amp;amp;sharedid=theverge.com" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Best Buy&lt;/a&gt;, with the majority of &lt;a href="https://www.microcenter.com/product/687907/amd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-granite-ridge-am5-470ghz-8-core-boxed-processor-heatsink-not-included"&gt;Micro Center&lt;/a&gt; locations also sold out of AMD’s best gaming processor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="NkINEZ"&gt;The situation is similar across Europe, too. In Germany most retailers have &lt;a href="https://x.com/3DCenter_org/status/1854705891209363749"&gt;run out of stock&lt;/a&gt;, with new shipments not expected to arrive until later this month. In the UK &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scan.co.uk%2Fproducts%2Famd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-am5-zen-5-8-core-16-thread-47ghz-52ghz-turbo-104mb-cache-pcie-50-120w-cpu&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F11%2F8%2F24291165%2Famd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-stock-sold-out" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Scan&lt;/a&gt; is accepting preorders for the 9800X3D, but stock won’t arrive until November 29th. &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.overclockers.co.uk%2Famd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-eight-core-5.20ghz-socket-am5-processor-retail-pro-amd-03517.html&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F11%2F8%2F24291165%2Famd-ryzen-7-9800x3d-stock-sold-out" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Overclockers&lt;/a&gt; in the UK says its stock is currently held at UK customs and that its first and second shipments are allocated and sold out. It’s not expecting another shipment until December.&lt;/p&gt;
